※※
# audit-sky-library

Manually-run workflow that lints every `.sky` file in a directory in one pass and
prints a pass/fail report grouped by file, exiting non-zero if any workflow fails.
Pure bash — no LLM tokens. The steward's pre-flight before sharing a library or in CI.

  (manual run: --var dir)
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  none found ──▶ note + stop (exit 0)
   │  scan  │
   └────────┘
       │ found N files
       ▼
   ┌──────────┐  for each: skyway lint → OK / FAIL + codes
   │ lint-all │
   └──────────┘
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐
   │ report │ ── grouped summary; exit 1 if any FAIL
   └────────┘

Run it (state which directory to audit with --var dir):

  skyway run audit-sky-library --var dir=".sky/workflows"

  - dir   directory of .sky files to lint — STATE THIS before running (e.g. .sky/workflows)
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "audit-sky-library"
description = "Lint every .sky in a directory in one pass and report pass/fail grouped by file, exiting non-zero on any failure. Fire via: skyway run audit-sky-library --var dir=<path>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
ui = "ui/workflow"
⊕⊕

※scan※
Scan directory for .sky files. Exit 0 if none found (not a failure).
※※

§scan§
bash_file = "./scripts/scan.sh"
ui = "ui/scan"
§§

※lint※
Lint each .sky file from scan. Tally pass/fail, exit non-zero if any fail. depends_on: scan (all_done, implicit).
※※

§lint§
depends_on = ["scan"]
bash_file = "./scripts/lint.sh"
ui = "ui/lint"
§§
